# One of fourteen Arabic letters that cause the "L" of a preceding definite article to be assimilated. Actually, the sun letter suppresses the sound of the "L" and then [[geminate]]s: al + sin = as-sin. The effect of the sun letter is limited to pronunciation and does not change the spelling: {{ARchar|[[الصين]]}}. The fourteen sun letters are:

::{{ARchar|[[ت]]}} , {{ARchar|[[ث]]}} , {{ARchar|[[د]]}} , {{ARchar|[[ذ]]}} , {{ARchar|[[ر]]}} , {{ARchar|[[ز]]}} , {{ARchar|[[س]]}} , {{ARchar|[[ش]]}} , {{ARchar|[[ص]]}} , {{ARchar|[[ض]]}} , {{ARchar|[[ط]]}} , {{ARchar|[[ظ]]}} , {{ARchar|[[ل]]}} , {{ARchar|[[ن]]}}

:The rest of the letters are [[moon letter]]s, which do not affect the pronunciation of the definite article.

